@ENDNODE

@NODE 4. "Requirements"
  You need at least OS 2.0 to run EuroTrash.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 5. "Installation"
  Use the included installer script to install EuroTrash. There is also a
  deinstaller script that you can use to remove EuroTrash from your system.

  If you don't have the installer utility, just open a shell and do the
  following:

    copy EuroTrash#? SYS:WBStartup

  If you have OS 2.1 or higher do this as well:

    copy Catalogs LOCALE: ALL

@ENDNODE

@NODE 6. "Program Usage"
  Drop drawers or files on the EuroTrash AppIcon to delete them. If there is
  a trashcan on the same volume as the dropped things, they will be moved to
  the trashcan instead.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 7. "Configuration"
  There are several tooltypes available for use in EuroTrash.info. These are:

    DONOTWAIT  - Ignore this one.

    LEFTEDGE   - Specify the X coordinate of where the AppIcon will appear.

    TOPEDGE    - Specify the Y coordinate of where the AppIcon will appear.

    ICONNAME   - This is the text that will appear beneath the trashcan
                 AppIcon.

    ICONFILE   - Specify a trashcan icon which EuroTrash will use instead of its
                 own. Leave out the ".info" extension.

    TRASHPATH  - This is the path where EuroTrash will look for the trashcan.
                 Address it relative to the current volume like this:
                 TRASHPATH=:trashcan

    ASK        - Yes or no. If yes, a requester will ask politely before
                 actually deleting anything. Moving to trashcan is always
                 quiet though.

@ENDNODE

